One popular application for children is the fishing game, tied on a piece of string to pick up pins and needles. The ferrite rings offer reduced magnetic strength, due to the hole, but the inexpensive pricing makes them a firm favourite. Some applications are: holding, door closures, joinery, light fixture.A ferrite is a ceramic material made by mixing and firing large proportions of iron(III) oxide (Fe2O3, rust) blended with small proportions of one or more additional metallic elements, such as barium, manganese, nickel, and zinc. They are both electrically non-conductive, meaning that they are insulators, meaning they can easily be magnetized or attracted to a magnet. Ferrite can be divided into two families based on their resistance to being demagnetized.Hard ferrite have high coercive force, so are difficult to demagnetize.
